hamiltonian.description:
Qubits are modelled as a two level system. Qubits are coupled through resonator buses. The provided Hamiltonian has been projected into the zero excitation subspace of the resonator buses leading to an effective qubit-qubit flip-flop interaction. The qubit resonance frequencies in the Hamiltonian are the cavity dressed frequencies and not exactly what is returned by the backend defaults, which also includes the dressing due to the qubit-qubit interactions.
Warning: Currently not all system Hamiltonian information is available to the public, missing values have been replaced with 0.
